Basic commands:
  az login           Log in to Azure
  az account         Manage azure subscription information
  az disk list       List all Azure Managed Disks
  az vm list         List all Azure virtual machines
  az aks             Manage Azure Kubernetes Services
  az network         Manage Azure Network resources
  az image list --output table         Show own images
  az disk list --output table         Show disks
  az account list-locations --output table        List supported regions for the current subscription.

Subscription:
  az account list             Get a list of subscriptions for the logged in account
  az account show             Get the details of a subscription
  az account set --subscription <mysubscription>    Set a subscription to be the current active subscription

VMs management:
  az vm list --output table                                              In table output
  az vm list -d --query "[?powerState=='VM running']" --output table     List only VMs having distinct state
  az vm delete -g MyRG -n MyLinuxVM --yes                                Delete VM (with the name MyLinuxVM in the group MyRG)
  az vm delete --ids $(az vm list -g MyRG --query "[].id" -o tsv)        Delete all VMs in a resource group

Storage management:
  az storage account list --output table                                              Show storage accounts
  az storage container list --account-name mystorageaccount --output table            Show containers for an account
  az storage blob list --account-name mystorageaccount \
    --container-name mycontainer  --output table                                      Show blobs in a container
  az storage account keys list  --account-name STORAGE_NAME --resource-group RESOURCE_GROUP            List account keys
  az configure --defaults location=eastus2                                            Configure default storage location

Network management:
  az network vnet list --output table                  List virtual networks
  az network nic list --output table                   List virtual networks adapters
  az vm list-ip-addresses --output table               List public IP addresses used by the VMs

Common commands:
  az snapshot create --resource-group IC-EXASOL-001 --source vm1-disk1 -n vm1-snap1         Create snapshot
  az snapshot grant-access --resource-group IC-EXASOL-001 --name vm1-snap1\
    --duration-in-seconds 36000 --query '[accessSas]' -o tsv                                Create SAS url for a snapshot
  az vm disk attach --vm-name vm1 -g RESOURCE_GROUP --disk DISK1_ID                         Attach disk
  az vm disk detach --vm-name vm1 -g RESOURCE_GROUP --name DISK1_ID                         Detach disk
  az vm open-port --resource-group MyRG --name MyLinuxVM --port 443 --priority 899          Open port

Copy blob:
  az storage blob copy start \
    --source-uri 'https://xxx.blob.core.windows.net/jzwuuuzzapn0/abcd?...' \
    --account-key XXXXXXXXXX== \
    --account-name destaccount \
    --destination-container vms \
    --destination-blob DESTINATION-blob.vhd

Create an Image based on a running VM:
  az vm deallocate -g MyRG -n MyLinuxVM
  az vm generalize -g MyRG -n MyLinuxVM
  az image create --resource-group MyRG --name MyTestImage --source MyLinuxVM

Check all users in the Azure AD tenant:
  az ad user list -o table

Create a resource group named MyRG in the westus2 region:
  az group create -n MyRG -l westus2

Create a Linux VM using the UbuntuTLS image, with two attached storage disks of 10 GB and 20 GB:
  az vm create -n MyLinuxVM -g MyRG \
    --ssh-key-value $HOME/.ssh/id_rsa.pub --image UbuntuLTS \
    --data-disk-sizes-gb 10 20

Running VM based on a VHD:
  az storage blob upload --account-name "${account_name}"  \
   --account-key "${account_key}" --container-name "${container}" --type page \
   --file "${file}" --name "${vhd}"
  az disk create \
   --resource-group "${resource_group}" \
   --name myManagedDisk \
   --source "https://${account_name}.blob.core.windows.net/${container}/${vhd}"


